# 1.0 Changelog

## Technical
+ Added a new system for adding block models

# 0.2.8.1 Changelog

+ Updated mod metadata
+ Added a config toggle for crafting sounds
+ Added a secret visual feature
+ Fixed a crash caused by using crates with an empty hand
+ Fixed crate AO rendering causing crates to appear very dark
+ Fixed vessel recipes not carrying over damage. Should work for modded vessels too
+ Fixed error output from recycling system
+ Fixed anvil recycling recipe
+ Removed fishing rods from being able to be recycled

# 0.2.8 Changelog
+ Tiered crate blocks, which store a mass amount of one item/block
+ Bags of holding, which grant the player a variable amount of additional inventory slots. They can be found as dungeon loot
+ New enchants: Feather Weight, Holding, Vacuum and Soulbound

## General
+ New integration with WAILA display
+ New integration with ManyLib config library
+ New integration with Baubles
+ Updated invisible stalker visuals; they are now completely invisible until you get close to them
+ Updated how smelting tools and armor works, result now scales based on ingredients used
+ Improved the way handpans and polearms are animated in first person
+ Improved how polearm entities are rendered
+ Improved mod compatibility overall
+ 11 new music tracks
+ Removed querns, their design has also been superseded by the recent tool bench changes
+ Removed the ability to toggle debug features without having cheats enabled. This covers hitboxes and durability tooltips
+ Fixed polearm entities desyncing with the client when killing a mob
+ Fixed EMI display with Renewed's tool bench scaling
+ Fixed "ghost shanks" and stat desyncs with difficulty changes
+ Fixed enum options not saving / being applied properly
+ Fixed YAML config not applying properly in dedicated servers

## Difficulty
+ Difficulty can now be changed from in-game, and is also available for LAN server hosts
+ Difficulty can now be locked during world creation, preventing changes after a world is made
+ Regeneration rate parameter: determines how fast you regenerate health
+ Exhaustion rate parameter: determines how fast you lose hunger
+ Armor protection parameter: scales how much armor protects player/mobs
+ Experience parameters: scale how much experience is given from various sources
+ Level bonus parameters: scales the bonuses given for each level, e.g. crafting speed and harvest speed
+ (Legendary) Players regen twice as fast. This is to remove downtime in combat scenarios (e.g. caving)
+ (Legendary) Players and mobs have 150% armor protection. Armored mobs are much harder to take down, but so are you
+ (Legendary) Mobs now drop twice the amount of experience they normally drop. This is to encourage fighting and make bouncing back from death a bit easier
+ Made tooltips for armor and tools reflect difficulty stat scaling
+ Polished up the custom difficulty menu some

## Crafting
+ Gem shards now give a tenth of their full gem equivalent's XP when used
+ Bowls are now crafted using a knife and wood plank
+ Slabs can now be crafted back into their full block equivalent
+ Bows can be crafted into two sticks
+ Bows can be crafted into string with a knife
+ Alternative biomass recipe made with 4 leaves

## Config
+ Config is now handled via ManyLib
+ Added a list toggle for music frequency, choose between four modes of frequency
+ Added a toggle for the music display
+ Added a value for HUD padding
+ Added toggle for the new loot beams
+ Added toggle for mob death "poof" sound

## Technical
+ JeffyLib is now integrated as a dependency for Renewed
+ Server packet/callback for when a player starts to mine a block
+ Packets for handling backpacks (carryover from Jeffy Backpacks)
+ Bulk item entity for large stacks (>64) of items
+ Rewrote internal tool recipe handler for better mod support
+ New tool recipe parser for EMI

Special thank you to Xy_Luce/Xy_Lose providing an updated Chinese translation!

# 0.2.7.2 Changelog
+ Updated some Renewed block and item art to match programmer art better
+ Fixed ladders being unclimbable in Legendary

# 0.2.7.1 Changelog
+ Fixed time adjustment method extending day and night time

# 0.2.7 Changelog
## [Difficulty]
+ Added a brand new difficulty system
+ Added two new difficulty presets: Hard and Legendary.
+ Added a difficulty customizer; tweak many different game parameters

## [Hard Mode]
An easier version of MiTE.
+ Starts with 5 hearts and hunger as minimum
+ Mining speed is increased by 50%
+ Mobs do 25% less damage to the player
+ Animals/Mobs will always drop their loot no matter the cause of death
+ Weather events do not occur until after the 16th day in a world
+ Cave-ins can no longer be caused by walking on unstable ground

## [Legendary Mode]
A more brutal version of MiTE.
+ Leaf blocks are non solid, gravity blocks break them
+ Vines can no longer be climbed, only used for descent
+ You earn a new heart and hunger pip per 7 levels (normally 5)
+ Your hearts and hunger cap out at 8
+ Mobs deal 50% more damage
+ The player deals 25% less damage
+ There is no weather grace period

## [General]
+ Workbenches now scale crafting speed based on tier, with huge increases in mithril and especially adamantium
+ Chickens now use worms as their breeding item; previously it was way too easy to scale up chicken farms
+ Revenants and Bone Lords sounds have been pitched down, for better audio indication of their presence
+ Weather events do not occur for 8 days when starting a world
+ Item frames and signs can now be placed on chests
+ Added an additional sound for when mobs "poof"
+ Tweaked how the ingame display is rendered; bottom elements are raised slightly towards the center
+ Fixed music display rendering leak, should no longer flicker when enchanted gear is in the inventory
+ Fixed buckets crashing when using other mods that add buckets (e.g. ITF)
+ Fixed buckets restoring themselves when making cheese and bowls of water

## [Stack Size Changes]
+ Increased stack size for ores (4 -> 8)
+ Increased stack size for glass (4 -> 8)
+ Increased stack size for bookshelves (4 -> 8)
+ Increased stack size for TNT (4 -> 8)
+ Increased stack size for wood slabs (8 -> 16)

# 0.2.6.3 Changelog
